00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:54.840
Translations.

00:14:54.840 --> 00:14:56.840
It's not as simple.

00:14:56.840 --> 00:14:59.580
I recognize it's not a simple task to have good translations

00:14:59.580 --> 00:14:59.840
.

00:14:59.840 --> 00:15:06.830
Machine translations can't be up to date with new popular ways

00:15:06.830 --> 00:15:08.840
to in terms across the internet.

00:15:08.840 --> 00:15:12.840
The language is moving really fast around the internet.

00:15:13.840 --> 00:15:16.840
So, the translation won't always keep up with that.

00:15:16.840 --> 00:15:20.840
I will give a little example in the next slide.

00:15:20.840 --> 00:15:26.200
Be cautious of relying on AI because you don't know if

00:15:26.200 --> 00:15:31.340
that model is well-trained in that language you want

00:15:31.420 --> 00:15:31.830
.

00:15:31.840 --> 00:15:39.840
There's multiple models that have different training and you

00:15:39.840 --> 00:15:46.840
can maybe have more problems relying on that than not.

00:15:46.840 --> 00:15:51.170
Localizing your app will make a huge difference, not just

00:15:51.170 --> 00:15:51.840
translating.

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:56.840
I will give a little bit of examples, but again,

00:15:56.840 --> 00:15:59.840
the next talk will go even deeper about this.

00:15:59.840 --> 00:16:06.820
My little example is from Twitter.

00:16:07.840 --> 00:16:14.530
So, in Brazil, tweets became tweets, right like that

00:16:14.530 --> 00:16:20.790
, and the users became known as twitteiros.

00:16:20.840 --> 00:16:25.470
Like, this kind of thing, a machine translator won't

00:16:25.470 --> 00:16:28.840
get for a long time.

00:16:28.840 --> 00:16:34.610
They might know now because Twitter is around for a couple of

00:16:34.700 --> 00:16:39.470
years now, but for new apps, you won't know

00:16:39.470 --> 00:16:41.840
by relying on machine translations.

00:16:41.840 --> 00:16:47.010
A little tips that I see a lot of people struggling around

00:16:47.010 --> 00:16:48.840
the atmosphere.

00:16:49.840 --> 00:16:50.840
Time zones.

00:16:50.840 --> 00:16:55.840
Please avoid using regional names for time zones.

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:56.330
U.

00:16:56.330 --> 00:16:56.840
S.

00:16:56.840 --> 00:16:58.840
Central doesn't mean anything in Brazil.

00:16:58.840 --> 00:16:59.840
Please.

00:17:00.840 --> 00:17:09.040
A good way to be safe is using U

00:17:09.070 --> 00:17:10.840
TC.

00:17:10.840 --> 00:17:13.840
UTC is the universal time for a reason.

00:17:13.840 --> 00:17:17.840
UTC is more easy to be understood around the globe.

00:17:17.840 --> 00:17:21.840
So, I give you this tip, it's easier.

00:17:21.840 --> 00:17:26.660
Because if you also want to list big cities, you will

00:17:26.660 --> 00:17:30.840
need a really, really huge list to maintain.

00:17:30.840 --> 00:17:36.920
And you might not be familiar with cities from different countries you

00:17:37.100 --> 00:17:38.840
never heard about.

00:17:39.840 --> 00:17:44.220
So, I think the good old UTC is a safe

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:46.820
bet to go for that.

00:17:46.840 --> 00:17:54.840
Now, let's talk about tools to help you translate.

00:17:54.840 --> 00:18:00.830
Because I know not everyone has a lot of money and multiple

00:18:01.100 --> 00:18:03.840
people inside their teams to help.

00:18:04.840 --> 00:18:08.910
So, you can use some tools to have the community to

00:18:08.910 --> 00:18:10.840
help you translate.

00:18:10.840 --> 00:18:14.900
This one NPM X is using, it's called Lun

00:18:14.900 --> 00:18:15.840
aria.

00:18:15.840 --> 00:18:22.190
You can see in this screenshot, you can see the translation

00:18:22.190 --> 00:18:23.840
from Portuguese.

00:18:24.840 --> 00:18:27.840
And there's 89 of the strings translated.

00:18:27.840 --> 00:18:33.520
So, there's need some updates and it lists how much

00:18:33.520 --> 00:18:35.840
, what you need to translate.

00:18:35.840 --> 00:18:38.840
Unfortunately, it's a little bit technical.

00:18:38.840 --> 00:18:44.680
You need to know how the people translating need to know how

00:18:44.680 --> 00:18:49.840
to commit and push code and find those strings.

00:18:50.840 --> 00:18:52.840
It's not that simple to use.

00:18:52.840 --> 00:19:00.840
There's this tool that is used by Tokimeki.

00:19:00.840 --> 00:19:04.840
It's a little bit easier to use.

00:19:04.840 --> 00:19:13.490
You can use this interface to see different strings from different languages

00:19:13.830 --> 00:19:14.840
to translate.

00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:19.840
But it requires a connection with GitHub.

00:19:19.840 --> 00:19:24.420
So, having a GitHub account, it's not something that

00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:26.840
non-devs are very familiar with.

00:19:26.840 --> 00:19:32.580
But when you have the GitHub account, you can do everything

00:19:32.600 --> 00:19:34.840
through this interface.

00:19:35.840 --> 00:19:40.410
But that is a point to note that might be a problem

00:19:40.410 --> 00:19:44.840
to gather help from non-technical people.

00:19:44.840 --> 00:19:50.840
And that is crowding that Blue Sky is using.

00:19:50.840 --> 00:19:53.840
It's really less technical.

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:57.840
You don't need to touch code at all.

00:19:58.840 --> 00:20:02.840
You just see the text and translate in the app.

00:20:02.840 --> 00:20:04.840
They have even mobile app.

00:20:04.840 --> 00:20:07.840
So, it's really, really easy to use.

00:20:07.840 --> 00:20:14.820
But also, they have some requirements to use this.

00:20:14.840 --> 00:20:18.840
So, check if your project can use this first.

